title: 2020 FA Cup Final
summary: The 2020 FA Cup Final, known officially as the Heads Up FA Cup Final, was an association football match played between Arsenal and Chelsea at Wembley Stadium, London, England, on 1 August 2020. Organised by the Football Association (FA), it was the 139th final of the Football Association Challenge Cup (FA Cup). Originally scheduled for 23 May, it was delayed due to the COVID-19 pandemic in the United Kingdom and played behind closed doors.
